XXXV. On account of the facility, the divine law given to the Hebrews punishes more heavily theft from the field than from the house 3 Exod. xxii. 1 and 7. So J ustin says the Scythians account theft a most heinous crime, in consequence of its facility among their unin- closed herds. So Aristotle.
